On 26.01.2013 21:22, juanmcc wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Hi Markus,
&gt;
&gt; I wanted to do something similar, so maybe my answers can help you.
&gt;
&gt; &gt; 1. For the initial start do I really have to use a seeds file or is
&gt; &gt; there a way to tell heritrix to check the actionfolder when the job is
&gt; &gt; started?
&gt;
&gt; If I&#39;m not missing something, Heritrix checks the action folder every 
&gt; time you start the job (in addition to the periodic checks, of course)
&gt;
&gt; &gt; 2. What possibilities do I have when the job finished before I can add
&gt; &gt; new seeds to the action dir or if the job finished before it checked 
&gt; the
&gt; &gt; action dir again?
&gt;
&gt; You can tell Heritrix to keep running a job even though there are no 
&gt; more URLs to crawl. To do that, just set to true the setting 
&gt; &#39;runWhileEmpty&#39; under the &#39;crawlController&#39; bean. For instance:
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; I think that&#39;s the only thing you need to keep crawling new URLs 
&gt; whenever you add new seeds to the action directory.
&gt;
&gt; Best,
&gt;
&gt; Juan Manuel Caicedo
&gt;
&gt; --- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com 
&gt; &lt;mailto:archive-crawler%40yahoogroups.com&gt;, &quot;Markus.Mirsberger&quot; wrote:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Hi,
