            &lt;p&gt;Hi Markus,&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              I wanted to do something similar, so maybe my answers can
              help you.&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              &gt; 1. For the initial start do I really have to use a
              seeds file or is &lt;br&gt;
              &gt; there a way to tell heritrix to check the
              actionfolder when the job is &lt;br&gt;
              &gt; started?&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              If I&#39;m not missing something, Heritrix checks the action
              folder every time you start the job (in addition to the
              periodic checks, of course)&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              &gt; 2. What possibilities do I have when the job finished
              before I can add &lt;br&gt;
              &gt; new seeds to the action dir or if the job finished
              before it checked the &lt;br&gt;
              &gt; action dir again?&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              You can tell Heritrix to keep running a job even though
              there are no more URLs to crawl. To do that, just set to
              true the setting &#39;runWhileEmpty&#39; under the
              &#39;crawlController&#39; bean. For instance:&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              I think that&#39;s the only thing you need to keep crawling
              new URLs whenever you add new seeds to the action
              directory.&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              Best,&lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
              Juan Manuel Caicedo &lt;br&gt;
              &lt;br&gt;
